\newlabel{fig:risk_coverage}{{7}{20}{Risk-coverage curve. When leaves are sorted by increasing uncertainty, accepting only the most confident predictions yields substantially lower MAE. The mean baseline (dashed) is beaten at coverages below ${\sim }60\%$}{figure.7}{}}
